<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,453,919]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis box="[151,728,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
Diagnosis (emended from 
<bibRefCitation author="Boury-Esnault" box="[469,712,453,478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133" refString="Boury-Esnault, N. (2002) Family Polymastiidae Gray, 1867. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera. A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Vol. 1. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, pp. 201 - 219." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Boury­Esnault 
<number box="[650,712,453,478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Sponges are cushion­shaped or discoid, with a single low oscular papilla. The edge of the body is very hispid whereas the other part of the surface is only minutely hispid. The choanosomal skeleton is composed by tracts of tylostyles, subtylostyles or styles which project beyond the surface making up the hispidation. The cortical skeleton includes a palisade of small tylostyles. Acanthose microxeas are very abundant both in cortex and choanosome.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,453,919]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis box="[198,476,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Emendations proposed:</emphasis>
<number box="[484,497,653,679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" value="1.0">1</number>
) Spicules of the choanosomal tracts may be styles. 
<number box="[1103,1119,653,679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" value="2.0">2</number>
) In all known 
<taxonomicName class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Acanthopolymastia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Acanthopolymastia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. the surface is hispid to a greater or lesser degree (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kelly-Borges" box="[972,1361,693,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" refString="Kelly-Borges, M. &amp; Bergquist, P. R. (1997) Revision of Southwest Pacific Polymastiidae (Porifera: Demospongiae: Hadromerida) with descriptions of new species of Polymastia Bowerbank, Tylexocladus Topsent, and Acanthopolymastia gen. nov. from New Zealand and the Norfolk Ridge, New Caledonia. New Zealand Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 31 (3), 367 - 402." type="journal article" year="1997">
Kelly­Borges &amp; Bergquist 
<number box="[1298,1361,693,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This hispidation is constituted by the choanosomal tracts projecting beyond the whole surface but not exclusively at the edge as given in Systema Porifera (
<bibRefCitation author="Boury-Esnault" box="[638,883,773,799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133" refString="Boury-Esnault, N. (2002) Family Polymastiidae Gray, 1867. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera. A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Vol. 1. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, pp. 201 - 219." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Boury­Esnault 
<number box="[819,883,773,799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, the excess edge hispidation shared by 
<taxonomicName authority="Koltun, 1964" authorityName="Koltun" authorityYear="1964" box="[189,529,813,839]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Acanthopolymastia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="acanthoxa">
<emphasis box="[189,345,813,838]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">A. acanthoxa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun" box="[362,521,813,839]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" refString="Koltun, V. M. (1964) Sponges of the Antarctic. Part 1. Tetraxonida and Cornacuspongida. In: Pavlovskii, E. P., Andriyashev, A. P. &amp; Ushakov, P. V. (Eds.), Biological Reports of the Soviet Antarctic Expedition (1955 - 1958), Explorations of the fauna of the seas. Vol. 2 (10). Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Nauka, Moscow-Leningrad, 6 - 133, 443 - 448." type="journal article" year="1964">
Koltun, 
<number box="[461,521,813,839]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Levi, 1993" authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1993" box="[589,896,813,839]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Acanthopolymastia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pisiformis">
<emphasis box="[589,740,813,838]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">A. pisiformis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Levi" box="[757,888,813,839]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" refString="Levi, C. (1993) Porifera Demospongiae: Spongiaires bathyaux de Nouvelle-Caledonie, recoltes par le ' Jean Charcot'. Campagne BIOCAL, 1985. In: Crosnier, A. (Ed.), Resultats des campagnes MUSORSTOM, Vol. 11. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle (A, Zoologie), 158, 9 - 87." type="journal article" year="1993">
Lévi, 
<number box="[828,888,813,839]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is not found in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kelly-Borges &amp; Bergquist, 1997" authorityName="Kelly-Borges &amp; Bergquist" authorityYear="1997" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Acanthopolymastia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bathamae">
<emphasis box="[1089,1239,813,838]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">A. bathamae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kelly-Borges" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" refString="Kelly-Borges, M. &amp; Bergquist, P. R. (1997) Revision of Southwest Pacific Polymastiidae (Porifera: Demospongiae: Hadromerida) with descriptions of new species of Polymastia Bowerbank, Tylexocladus Topsent, and Acanthopolymastia gen. nov. from New Zealand and the Norfolk Ridge, New Caledonia. New Zealand Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 31 (3), 367 - 402." type="journal article" year="1997">
Kelly­Borges &amp; Bergquist, 
<number box="[278,340,853,879]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
